<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10102310>
    dc:description "Figs. 1–6. Dorsal and ventral habiti of Monolepta spp. 1) M. mandibularis, dorsal view; 2) M. mandibularis, ventral view; 3) M. meihuai, dorsal view; 4) M. meihuai, ventral view; 5–6) M. meihuai, color variations." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10102310/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10102312>
    dc:description "Figs. 7–15. Monolepta mandibularis. 7) Median lobe, dorsal view; 8) Median lobe, lateral view; 9) Median lobe, ventral view; 10) Male antennomeres I-IV; 11) Male antenna; 12) Female antenna; 13) Ventral bursa-sclerites; 14) Spermatheca; 15) Dorsal bursa-sclerites. Figs. 7–9 drawn to same scale; Figs. 11 and 12 drawn to same scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10102312/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10102314>
    dc:description "Figs. 16–18. Spiculae of endophallus of Monolepta spp. 16) M. mandibularis; 17) M. gracilipes; 18) M. meihuai." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10102314/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10102318>
    dc:description "Figs. 19–21. Field observations. 19–20) Monolepta mandibularis; 21) Monolepta meihuai." ;
